Solution Brief:

The Architecture and System Design Libraries Recommendation System is a collaborative platform that streamlines onboarding at Pfizer. By intelligently matching project queries with a curated database of libraries and integrating real-time user feedback, the system recommends the most relevant tools and frameworks that align with Pfizer’s tech stack. This approach ensures consistency across projects, accelerates onboarding, and enhances efficiency by reducing the time spent on manual library research—supporting both established and innovative technologies for scalable, client-focused solutions.


Solution Brief:

Our system is a collaborative tool that helps new joiners at Pfizer quickly find the right libraries and tools for their projects. By matching user queries with a curated database and using real-time feedback, it speeds up onboarding, ensures consistent tech stack use, and boosts development efficiency.
